UPDATE public.courses SET curriculum = '[{"year":"Core Subjects","modules":["Below is a concise, rephrased English version formatted like an academic program or list of specializations within a Business degree.","Business Major — Common Specializations","Actuarial ScienceApply probability, statistics and finance to assess and manage risk in insurance, pensions and social programs. Learn data analysis, forecasting, risk table construction and computational methods for research and decision-making.","EconomicsStudy the production, distribution and consumption of goods and services and how individuals and institutions allocate scarce resources. Develop skills in economic research, data analysis, trend monitoring and forecasting for issues such as inflation, interest and exchange rates, employment and public policy.","FinanceFocus on the management and allocation of financial resources for individuals, firms and markets. Topics include corporate and investment banking, budgeting and forecasting, asset–liability management, capital markets, stocks and bonds, and financial institutions’ operations.","International BusinessExamine the structures and institutions that shape the global economy. Coursework covers international economics, global finance, cross-border management, trade law, information systems and international marketing.","ManagementLearn principles and practices for planning, organizing, staffing, leading and controlling organizations. Emphasis on systems thinking, organizational behavior, strategic decision-making and effective managerial practices.","MarketingExplore methods to identify and satisfy consumer and business needs for products and services. Study market research, consumer behavior, product development, pricing strategy, promotion and distribution to design and implement competitive marketing programs.","If you want this as part of a syllabus, course catalog entry, or with suggested core courses for each specialization, tell me which format you prefer."]}]'::jsonb, entry_requirements_text = NULL WHERE id = '91344bff-907c-479e-a1d8-ec3c019eb25e';
UPDATE public.courses SET curriculum = '[{"year":"Core Subjects","modules":["Computer Science Major","Study the design, testing, maintenance and evolution of software and computing systems. Emphasis on mathematical and theoretical foundations of computing, practical programming skills, and staying current with rapid technological change.","Artificial IntelligenceExplore methods that enable machines to reason, learn and perceive. Topics include machine learning, neural networks, natural language processing, computer vision, and intelligent agents for automation and decision support.","Computer GraphicsStudy the theory and practice of generating visual content with computers. Covers rendering, modeling, animation, visualization, GPU programming and tools for film, simulation and interactive media.","Computer Gaming (Game Development)Focus on the design and technical development of interactive games. Includes game engine architecture, real-time graphics, physics, gameplay design, storytelling, UI/UX, and production workflows.","Computer NetworksLearn to design, deploy and manage networked systems and infrastructure. Topics include network protocols, routing and switching, security, wireless and cloud networking, and systems administration, plus management skills for technical teams.","Software DevelopmentCover the software lifecycle: requirements, design, implementation, testing, maintenance and evolution. Emphasis on software engineering principles, programming languages, development methodologies (Agile/DevOps), quality assurance and tooling.","If you want this expanded into a course catalog entry with suggested core and elective courses for each specialization, or translated into Arabic, tell me which format you prefer."]}]'::jsonb, entry_requirements_text = NULL WHERE id = '936eb4f4-dd48-47af-b569-934df47408df';
UPDATE public.courses SET curriculum = '[{"year":"Core Subjects","modules":["Engineering Major","Engineers apply science, mathematics, analysis and synthesis to design practical, efficient solutions within constraints of time, cost, safety and health. The degree prepares graduates for roles in design, research, operation and project management across industries.","Aerospace (Aeronautical) EngineeringStudy aircraft and spacecraft design, aerodynamics, airfoil and control-surface design, lift and drag, and flight/spacecraft systems. Covers aerodynamic behavior, propulsion basics and vehicle control.","Applied ScienceApply natural science principles to solve practical problems and develop technology. Prepares students for science careers and professional/graduate studies (e.g., medicine, pharmacy, optometry, veterinary, physical therapy).","Chemical / Petroleum EngineeringFocus on the exploration, extraction and production of oil and gas, and on chemical process engineering. Emphasizes reservoir evaluation, drilling supervision, production optimization, environmental safety and development of extraction technologies.","Civil EngineeringDesign, construct and maintain built and natural environments. Specializations include structural, geotechnical, transportation, water resources, environmental, urban/coastal engineering, materials engineering, surveying and construction management.","Electrical / Electronic EngineeringStudy electricity, electronics and electromagnetism. Topics include power systems, transmission and distribution, control systems, signal processing, telecommunications, integrated circuits and electronic device design.","Mechanical EngineeringCover mechanics, kinematics, thermodynamics, heat transfer, fluid mechanics, robotics, structural analysis and technical drafting. Emphasis on design, energy conversion, machine systems and mechanical product development.","If you’d like this presented as a course catalog entry, with suggested core and elective courses for each specialization, or translated into Arabic, tell me which option you prefer."]}]'::jsonb, entry_requirements_text = NULL WHERE id = 'a0a046c9-414c-4aba-8bac-9da91e29801d';
